en_954499_0	12 fundamental rights petitions have been filed in the Supreme Court against the implementation of the death penalty.
en_954499_1	It includes the Centre for Policy Alternatives.
en_954499_2	The petitioners are seeking an interim injunction to prevent the implementation of the death penalty, a decision taken by the President to enforce the death penalty on four prisoners.
en_954499_3	They say that the death penalty is to be enforced through the Prisons Commissioner and the Welikada Prisons Superintendent.
en_954499_4	They are of the view that the implementation of the death penalty violates human rights.
en_954499_5	The petitioners are seeking an order saying that the decision concerned violates the fundamental rights of everyone, which are similar in the face of the law as mentioned in the Constitution.
